## All Basic Git & GitHub Commands

---

### 🔧 Setup (First Time)
```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@email.com"

# Check your config
git config --list
```

---

### 📁 Starting a Repo
```bash
# Start a new repo in current folder
git init

# Clone an existing repo from GitHub
git clone https://github.com/username/repo-name.git

# Clone into a specific folder name
git clone https://github.com/username/repo.git my-folder
```

---

### 📝 Staging & Committing
```bash
# Check what's changed
git status

# Stage a specific file
git add filename.js

# Stage everything
git add .

# Commit staged files
git commit -m "your message"

# Stage + commit tracked files in one step
git commit -am "your message"

# Fix last commit message (before pushing)
git commit --amend -m "corrected message"
```

---

### 🌿 Branches
```bash
# See all branches
git branch

# Create a new branch
git branch feature-login

# Switch to a branch
git checkout feature-login

# Create + switch in one step (most common)
git checkout -b feature-login

# Modern way to switch
git switch feature-login

# Delete a branch (after merging)
git branch -d feature-login

# Force delete a branch
git branch -D feature-login
```

---

### 🔀 Merging & Rebasing
```bash
# Merge a branch into current branch
git merge feature-login

# Rebase current branch onto main
git rebase main

# Abort a merge conflict
git merge --abort
```

---

### 🌐 Remote (GitHub)
```bash
# Connect local repo to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git

# See connected remotes
git remote -v

# Push to GitHub
git push origin main

# Push a new branch to GitHub
git push -u origin feature-login

# Pull latest changes from GitHub
git pull origin main

# Fetch changes without merging
git fetch origin
```

---

### 📜 Viewing History
```bash
# Full commit history
git log

# Clean one-line history
git log --oneline

# Visual branch graph
git log --oneline --graph --all

# Last 5 commits
git log -5

# See changes in a specific commit
git show a1b2c3d
```

---

### 🔍 Comparing Changes
```bash
# See unstaged changes
git diff

# See staged changes (before commit)
git diff --staged

# Compare two branches
git diff main..feature-login
```

---

### ↩️ Undoing Things
```bash
# Unstage a file (keep changes)
git restore --staged filename.js

# Discard changes in a file (permanent!)
git restore filename.js

# Undo last commit (keep changes staged)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# Undo last commit (keep changes unstaged)
git reset --mixed HEAD~1

# Undo last commit (delete changes permanently!)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# Revert a commit (safe, creates new commit)
git revert a1b2c3d
```

---

### 🗃️ Stashing (Save Work Temporarily)
```bash
# Stash current changes
git stash

# See all stashes
git stash list

# Apply last stash
git stash pop

# Apply a specific stash
git stash apply stash@{2}

# Drop a stash
git stash drop stash@{0}
```

---

### 🏷️ Tags
```bash
# Create a tag
git tag v1.0.0

# Create an annotated tag
git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "version 1.0.0"

# Push tags to GitHub
git push origin --tags

# List all tags
git tag
```

---

### 🧹 Cleaning Up
```bash
# Remove untracked files (dry run first!)
git clean -n

# Actually remove untracked files
git clean -f

# Remove untracked files + folders
git clean -fd
```

---

### 🚀 Typical Daily Workflow
```bash
# 1. Pull latest
git pull origin main

# 2. Create a branch
git checkout -b feature-something

# 3. Make changes, then stage + commit
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add something"

# 4. Push branch to GitHub
git push -u origin feature-something

# 5. Open a Pull Request on GitHub, merge, done!
```

---

### 💡 Quick Reference Card

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `git init` | Start a new repo |
| `git clone` | Copy a repo |
| `git status` | See current changes |
| `git add .` | Stage everything |
| `git commit -m` | Save a snapshot |
| `git push` | Upload to GitHub |
| `git pull` | Download from GitHub |
| `git branch` | List branches |
| `git checkout -b` | New branch |
| `git merge` | Combine branches |
| `git log --oneline` | View history |
| `git stash` | Save work temporarily |
| `git reset --soft` | Undo commit (keep changes) |

